<p>Indoor air quality considerations are important in Pennsylvania due to seasonal allergens, industrial emissions in certain areas, and the need to maintain proper humidity levels during both heating and cooling seasons. Modern HVAC systems should incorporate advanced filtration, humidity control, and ventilation features to address these regional air quality concerns while maintaining energy efficiency.</p>

